{{Quote|You there, get me the tuning stylus."<br />"Yes, sir."<br />"No, no, no. I said the tuning stylus, you idiot!|8t88 asks Rol for a tuning stylus, but gets a testing probe instead|<ref name="Audio Drama">[[Dark Forces: Rebel Agent (audio drama)|''Dark Forces: Rebel Agent'' audio drama]]</ref>}}
A '''tuning stylus''' was a device used by [[roboticist]]s for adjusting [[Droid/Legends|droid]] machinery.

After the [[Droid/Legends|droid]] [[Information broker/Legends|informant]] [[8t88/Legends|8t88]] [[Mission_to_Nar_Shaddaa_(5_ABY)|lost]] an [[Limb/Legends|arm]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]]<ref name="RA" /> during the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]],<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of ''[[Dark Forces: Rebel Agent]]'' to the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]].</ref> [[Gender/Legends|he]] retreated to the [[Government House (Sulon)|Government House]] on the moon [[Sulon/Legends|Sulon]] for business related to the [[Imperial Remnant]]. An arm was transported to him from a fellow [[Model 88-series administration droid]], but lacking a qualified roboticist, he had to attach it to his own body. 8t88 asked his [[Bodyguard/Legends|bodyguard]] [[Rol (Human)|Rol]] to hand him a tuning stylus from an array of tools laid before him, but Rol instead picked a [[testing probe]], as he could not tell the difference between the two tools. 8t88 angrily discarded the testing probe and used the tuning stylus to finish his job with.<ref name="RA">''[[Dark Forces: Rebel Agent]]''</ref><ref name="Audio Drama" />

